<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-04-08</DATELINE><TITLE>Death and contagious infectious diseases: Impact of the COVID-19 virus on stock market returns</TITLE><BODY>Abstract This study investigates whether contagious infectious diseases affect stock market outcomes. As a natural experiment, we use panel data regression analysis to measure the effect of the COVID-19 virus, which is a contagious infectious disease, on the Chinese stock market. The findings indicate that both the daily growth in total confirmed cases and in total cases of death caused by COVID-19 have significant negative effects on stock returns across all companies.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>